Reasoning: The paper discusses the network of international co-authorship relations in science, which involves the use of data analysis and visualization techniques. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.DL (Digital Libraries), cs.SD (Software Engineering), cs.CY (Computers and Society), and cs.SY (Systems and Control). Among these, cs.SI is the most likely category as it directly relates to the network analysis aspect of the paper. The other categories are also relevant as they involve aspects of data analysis, information management, and social implications of technology.
